				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I figured out what's causing items 16+ to be invisible and 32 to crash it. The line buffer used by the VWF code is 128 bytes (16 tiles) long, at $0100-$017F. Data written past $0180 never gets copied to VRAM, and data written past $01F8 overlaps return addresses. I changed <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">load_item_shapes</tt> in <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">bg.s</tt> to copy glyphs to VRAM after each line of 16, and it handled 27 NKIs with no sweat. Moving <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">item_typehi</tt> and <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">item_shape</tt> from zero page to BSS let me push 47.</div>

					
